The paper discusses a method for identifying and monitoring wireless network devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also evaluates network parameters and their ability to identify devices, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) or cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the dependency of inter-arrival times on device characteristics, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) due to the potential impact on network performance for multimedia applications.
